</figure>
<p class="chakra-text css-en-pr2tx6">you can check the holey array in your Chrome Console, so if we write this <code class="chakra-code css-en-4m8w8z" node="[object Object]">new Array(10)</code> your console will display
<code class="chakra-code css-en-4m8w8z" node="[object Object]">[empty × 10]</code> which is an array of empty values.</p>
<p class="chakra-text css-en-pr2tx6">More Resources:</p>
<ol>
<style data-emotion="css-en klhzfh">.css-en-klhzfh{margin-bottom:var(--chakra-space-2);-webkit-margin-start:var(--chakra-space-4);margin-inline-start:var(--chakra-space-4);}</style><li class="chakra-text css-en-klhzfh"><a class="chakra-link css-en-ccuis4" href="https://v8.dev/blog/elements-kinds" node="[object Object]">https://v8.dev/blog/elements-kinds</a></li>
